Key Match Events: Raptors point guard Immanuel Quickley was a step ahead of Keon Johnson of the Nets for a loose ball in Wednesday night’s game at Scotiabank Arena.
Post-Match Reflections: The Raptors point guard wasn’t in mid-season form against the Nets after missing 22 games, but his impact was enormous at Scotiabank Arena.
Eventually the Raptors will get Immanuel Quickley in top shape, at his best, controlling his team.
What they need now from the young point guard is his presence, his effervescence, his will.
